==Transportation==
'''{{Colour|red|Warning}}:''' The entrance to the [[King Black Dragon Lair]] (aka '''KBD Lair''') is located in the [[Wilderness]]; '''watch out for player killers!'''
[[File:KBD Routes.png|thumb|left|300px|The routes that lead up to the KBD lair.]]
'''Note:''' After climbing down the ladder near the [[lesser demon]]s, players must pull a lever surrounded by [[poisonous spider]]s to access the lair.

*The [[burning amulet]] teleports the player to the [[Lava Maze]] just south-east of the fenced area containing the entrance to the lair. This is the fastest and most reliable method of getting there.
*[[Wilderness Obelisk]]s can be used, but be wary that using them will make encountering high-level monsters or [[PKers]] more likely. Players who have completed the [[hard Wilderness Diary]] can choose the obelisk they wish to teleport to, namely the obelisk closest to the lair at level 44 Wilderness. The nearest obelisk can be accessed if the player teleports to the [[Corporeal Beast]] area via a [[games necklace]], exits the cave, and runs south-east to the obelisk and then south-east again.
*From [[Edgeville]], players can make a [[waka canoe]] (requires 57 [[Woodcutting]]) at the canoe station and take it to the Wilderness. Upon arrival, the player will have to trek westward past some [[green dragon]]s on the southern end of the Lava Maze before going slightly north-west toward the western part of the maze.
*North-west of [[Ardougne Castle]], there's a [[Lever (Ardougne)|lever]] that takes the player to the [[Deserted Keep]]. From there, after slashing the [[web]]s, head southward to a long fence and follow it either east or west to an opening. If following it east, '''beware of the [[Chaos Elemental]].''' Once out, trek westward past the northern end of the Lava Maze before going slightly south-west toward the western part of the maze.
*The [[Ice Plateau Teleport|Ice Plateau]] or [[Ghorrock Teleport]] is among the fastest ways to get there. After teleporting, run south-east.
*The [[Arceuus spellbook]]'s [[Cemetery Teleport]] teleports players to the [[Forgotten Cemetery]], just south.

==Fight overview==
{{Main|King Black Dragon/Strategies}}
[[File:Fighting the King Black Dragon.png|thumb|280px|A group of players take on the King Black Dragon.]]
The King Black Dragon uses melee and [[dragonfire]], which is of a higher tier compared to those made by adult chromatic dragons. It makes use of four different breath attacks; normal dragonfire alongside three special dragonfire attacks; shock, ice, and poison. While the special dragonfire deals less damage than its normal dragonfire, they require more tiers of protection to reduce its damage, and even with full protection, can still deal up to 10 damage onto the player. Without any protection, the normal dragonfire can deal up to 65 damage and special dragonfire 50.

The special dragonfire attacks have a chance of applying a second effect on the player when it hits them. Shock dragonfire reduces all of the player's stats by two, poison dragonfire can inflict [[poison]] starting at 8 if not protected against, and ice dragonfire freezes the player for 10 ticks (6.0 seconds). Even in melee distance, the King Black Dragon is more likely to use dragonfire attacks.

